---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import CodeExample from '../../components/CodeExample.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Dice Notation - Getting Started"
  description="Learn RANDSUM dice notation from basics to advanced modifiers. Complete guide with examples."
  keywords={['dice notation', 'tutorial', 'guide', 'modifiers', 'RANDSUM']}
>
  <div class="notation-guide-page">
    <section class="guide-header">
      <div class="container">
        <nav class="breadcrumbs">
          <a href="/">Home</a> / <a href="/getting-started">Getting Started</a> / Dice Notation
        </nav>
        <h1>Dice Notation</h1>
        <p class="guide-description">
          Learn how to write dice notation expressions in RANDSUM. From basic rolls to complex modifiers.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="guide-content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h2>Basic Syntax</h2>
          <p>RANDSUM uses the standard dice notation format: <code>NdS</code> where N is quantity and S is sides.</p>

          <CodeExample
            code={`import { roll } from '@randsum/roller'

// Roll 1d20
roll('1d20')

// Roll 2d6
roll('2d6')

// Roll 4d8
roll('4d8')`}
            language="typescript"
            title="Basic Rolls"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="guide-section">
          <h2>Drop Modifiers</h2>
          <p>Drop lowest or highest dice from your roll:</p>

          <CodeExample
            code={`// D&D ability score: 4d6, drop lowest
roll('4d6L')

// Drop highest (disadvantage)
roll('4d6H')

// Drop 2 lowest
roll('4d6L2')`}
            language="typescript"
            title="Drop Modifiers"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="guide-section">
          <h2>Advantage and Disadvantage</h2>
          <p>Common D&D patterns using drop modifiers:</p>

          <CodeExample
            code={`// Advantage: roll 2d20, keep highest
roll('2d20L')

// Disadvantage: roll 2d20, keep lowest
roll('2d20H')`}
            language="typescript"
            title="Advantage/Disadvantage"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="guide-section">
          <h2>Arithmetic Modifiers</h2>
          <p>Add or subtract from your roll total:</p>

          <CodeExample
            code={`// Add modifier
roll('1d20+5')

// Subtract modifier
roll('2d6-1')

// Multiple operations
roll('1d20+3-1')`}
            language="typescript"
            title="Arithmetic"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="guide-section">
          <h2>Reroll Modifiers</h2>
          <p>Reroll dice matching certain conditions:</p>

          <CodeExample
            code={`// Reroll 1s
roll('4d6R{1}')

// Reroll results below 3
roll('4d6R{<3}')

// Reroll specific values
roll('4d20R{1,20}')`}
            language="typescript"
            title="Reroll Modifiers"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="guide-section">
          <h2>Exploding Dice</h2>
          <p>Roll extra dice on maximum results:</p>

          <CodeExample
            code={`// Exploding d6
roll('3d6!')

// Each 6 rolls another die`}
            language="typescript"
            title="Exploding Dice"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="guide-section">
          <h2>Combining Modifiers</h2>
          <p>You can chain multiple modifiers together:</p>

          <CodeExample
            code={`// Reroll 1s, then drop lowest, then add 2
roll('4d6R{1}L+2')

// Exploding dice with drop
roll('3d6!L')`}
            language="typescript"
            title="Combining Modifiers"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="guide-section">
          <h2>Multiple Dice Groups</h2>
          <p>Roll different dice types in a single expression:</p>

          <CodeExample
            code={`// Attack roll + damage
roll('1d20+5', '2d6+3')

// Or in a single string
roll('1d20+2d6+5')`}
            language="typescript"
            title="Multiple Groups"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="guide-section">
          <h2>Next Steps</h2>
          <ul class="next-steps-list">
            <li><a href="/getting-started/game-packages">Learn about game packages</a></li>
            <li><a href="/playground">Try notation in the playground</a></li>
            <li><a href="/packages/roller">Read full notation documentation</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/RANDSUM/randsum">View on GitHub</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .notation-guide-page {
    padding: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
  }

  .guide-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
    border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .breadcrumbs {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-alt);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .breadcrumbs a {
    color: var(--color-text-alt);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumbs a:hover {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .guide-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .guide-description {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-alt);
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .guide-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .guide-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);
  }

  .guide-section h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    padding-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .guide-section p {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
  }

  .next-steps-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .next-steps-list li {
    padding: var(--spacing-sm) 0;
  }

  .next-steps-list li a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .next-steps-list li a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
